Subject "Live Sound Mixing" gives an overview of the equipment and systems needed for live mixing, their basic structure, classification, working principles and main use. Practice takes place at the events organized by organizations that have entered into a relevant contract with the UT VCA.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Aims of the subject:
Explaining the work and application principles of the equipment and recording devices needed for live sound mixing, acquiring major working methods. Establishing theoretical base for practical courses in the program.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course student:
knows basic structure, working principles and sequence of the equipment needed for the live sound mixing, knows block schema,
knows main mixing consoles (both analogue and digital), is able to plan independently live sound mixing, considering the type and size of the event
